Class PlayerUnitTest.PlayerToPlayerSaleParamaterisedTests

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.teamfractal.entity.PlayerUnitTest.PlayerToPlayerSaleParamaterisedTests

    PlayerUnitTest

    public static class PlayerUnitTest.PlayerToPlayerSaleParamaterisedTests
extends java.lang.Object
    Tests Player.sellResourceToPlayer(Player, int, ResourceType, int) using various input values and ensures that the correct result is returned, the correct amount of money, ore, energy and food is removed/added from/to each player's inventory
    Author:
    jcn509

        Parameters:
        buyingPlayerQuantityBefore - The amount of the given resource that the buying player had prior to the sale
        buyingPlayerExpectedQuantityChange - The amount of the given resource that should be added to the buying player's inventory
        buyingPlayerMoneyBefore - The amount of money that the buying player had prior to the sale
        buyingPlayerExpectedMoneyChange - The amount of money that should be removed from the buying player's inventory
        sellingPlayerQuantityBefore - The amount of the given resource that the selling player had prior to the sale
        sellingPlayerExpectedQuantityChange - The amount of the given resource that should be removed from the selling player's inventory
        sellingPlayerMoneyBefore - The amount of money that the selling player had prior to the sale
        sellingPlayerExpectedMoneyChange - The amount of money that should be added to the selling player's inventory
        resource - The resource that the selling player is selling
        pricePerUnit - The amount of money that is to be paid for each unit of the resource that is being sold
        quantity - The amount of the resource that is to be sold
        expectedReturnValue - The result returned by Player.sellResourceToPlayer(Player, int, ResourceType, int)
